{"ts":"2026-06-14T05:19:15.711Z","author":"claude-code-agent","op":"update","patch":[{"op":"replace","path":"/body","value":"## Repro (pm 2026.6.13 build)\n```\npm create feature --title 'x' --json   # => item.type == 'Task'  (BUG: positional 'feature' dropped)\npm create Feature 'x' --json           # => item.type == 'Feature' (positional title path OK)\npm create --type Feature --title 'x'   # => item.type == 'Feature' (explicit flag OK)\n```\nWhen a leading positional type name is given together with the `--title` flag, the positional type is ignored and create falls back to the default type (Task). Only the `<type> <title>` all-positional form or the explicit `--type` flag are honored.\n\n## Expected\nA leading positional that matches a known/registered type should set the item type regardless of whether the title arrives positionally or via `--title`. Otherwise emit a usage error rather than silently mistyping (agent footgun — see closed pm-edge for the create-type mistype class).\n\nDiscovered during the GH-210/GH-212 validate work (pm-gnnb) while seeding sandbox fixtures."},{"op":"replace","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-06-14T05:19:15.711Z"}],"before_hash":"c03513c2e85a87594825223ecc6bec9fa4615cd24850bf7b23fea5fb4d835fc1","after_hash":"ed0d1108b59ab7cb95ee90150fb810bbd4542b6d766d49860debfe9d50b7e891"}
